on is non-other than Bulawayo City Council. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-604669" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-18.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-18.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-18-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> The Education sector was well represented at the exhibition. The winner is the Ministry of Primary and Secondary Education. The SMEs sector’s best stand goes to Zanu PF <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-604665" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-20.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-20.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-20-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" />    15:44 – President Mnangagwa is now presenting prizes to best stands at the exhibition. The best Zimbabwe exhibit in energy category is Verify Engineering. The winner for First-time Exhibitor is ED Men Believes. The best exhibit in Tourism and Travel is ZimParks. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-604660" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-17.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-17.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-17-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-604662" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-16.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-16.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/04/Tour-16-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw,